article.headline: Austin Peay 85, Tenn.-Martin 76
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. -- Wes Channels scored 23 points to lead Austin Peay to an 85-76 win over Tennessee-Martin on Thursday night. Drake Reed added 17 points and Caleb Brown chipped in with 13 for the Governors (8-7, 4-1 Ohio Valley Conference), who never trailed in the game. Channels went 5-for-9 from beyond the arc and Brown was 3-for-4 for Austin Peay, which was 10 of 17 from long range (58.8 percent) in the win. Lester Hudson led the Skyhawks (8-6, 1-3) with 34 points and Delrico Lane added 10. Hudson was 5 of 16 from 3-point range, and the Skyhawks were 7 of 28 as a team from behind the arc (25 percent). The Governors shot 54.7 percent from the field (29 of 53) compared to a 40.6 percent mark (26 of 64) for the Skyhawks.
